The  Bank of Japan  is set to keep policy on hold
on Thursday, and refrain from adding to the unprecedented easing unveiled in
April, a Bloomberg News survey of 34 economists shows.  The central bank is scheduled to release an updated outlook for growth
and inflation after the meeting on Thursday.  To contact the reporters on this story:
